                        <h2>What is the Turtle Shelter Project?</h2>
                        <p>
                            The Turtle Shelter Project started with a high-tech yet simple solution designed to help save lives. Inspired by the need for portable shelter, much like a turtle carries its shell, the project creates vests, aimed to provide essential warmth and protection to those experiencing homelessness. After losing seven friends to the harsh winter cold during her own time on the streets, our founder Jen found a way to make a difference. The Turtle Shelter Project creates affordable, high-tech foam vests that keep people warm in temperatures as low as 10 degrees below zero, offering a life-saving solution to alleviate suffering. The project invites individuals, businesses, and communities to get involved by requesting vests or organizing efforts to create and distribute them, making a real impact on the lives of those in need.
